Azimio la Umoja presidential aspirant Raila Odinga will on Saturday continue his Kakamega campaigns. This follows a day-long engagement in the county that is perceived his stronghold and has primarily voted for him in previous elections. On Friday, Raila and his running mate Martha Karua campaigned in the county ahead of the August 9n polls. Deputy President William Ruto will on the other hand take his campaign to Turkana county where is expected to sell his Kenya Kwanza plan for the country. Ruto's campaign will start in Lokori in Turkana East, proceed to Lokichar in Turkana South constituency, and finally Turkwel in Loima constituency. The second in command on Friday took his campaigns to Nakuru county where he campaigned for his presidency. Ruto started off with a prayer meeting in Nakuru where he met the clergy alongside area leaders.